# THEMES Domain Rules
# ===================
# Two separate color themes that must stay cohesive.

THEMES_RULE_0=Web UI uses GitHub Dark theme defined in src/app.css @theme block as Tailwind v4 CSS variables
THEMES_RULE_1=Web UI tokens: --color-bg #0d1117, --color-surface #161b22, --color-surface2 #1c2129, --color-border #30363d, --color-text #e6edf3, --color-text-dim #8b949e, --color-accent #58a6ff, --color-green #3fb950, --color-red #f85149, --color-orange #d29922, --color-purple #bc8cff
THEMES_RULE_2=HTML export uses Catppuccin Mocha inline CSS in src/cli/export-html.ts: bg #1e1e2e, surface #181825, text #cdd6f4, text-dim #a6adc8, border #313244, blue #89b4fa, green #a6e3a1, red #f38ba8
THEMES_RULE_3=When changing theme tokens, update BOTH the Tailwind theme in app.css AND the inline CSS in export-html.ts
THEMES_RULE_4=Badge classes generated by src/lib/utils/status.ts - statusBadgeClass, sessionStatusBadgeClass
THEMES_RULE_5=Mermaid uses 'dark' theme in web UI but 'default' theme in export - this is a known inconsistency
THEMES_RULE_6=Export HTML inlines all styles - no external CSS dependency. Keep it self-contained.
